==Walkthrough==

===Starting out===
{{Needed|None.}}
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Martin the Master Gardener]] in [[Draynor Village]]. {{Chat option|2Quest.|1Anything I can help with?|1}}
*Talk to 5 [[Group of Advanced Gardeners]] members. They are any of the gardeners found near farming patches that tend to your crops. Any of them will work except for [[Ayesha]] in [[Al Kharid]], and ones found on [[Great Kourend]]. '''Note:''' The following is ''A'' path you can take to speak to farmers quickly:
**Run north-west and talk to [[Elstan]] Allotment/Flower/Herb patch. {{Chat option|1Are you a member of the Group of Advanced Gardeners?}}
***If you do not have secateurs or a spade, buy them from the farm shop.
**Run south and talk to [[Frizzy Skernip]]. {{Chat option|1Are you a member of the Group of Advanced Gardeners?}}
**[[Spirit tree|GE Spirit Tree]] teleport to [[Gnome Stronghold]], run east and talk to [[Bolongo]]. {{Chat option|1Are you a member of the Group of Advanced Gardeners?}}
**Run south-west and talk to [[Prissy Scilla]] at the tree patch. {{Chat option|1Are you a member of the Group of Advanced Gardeners?}}
**Teleport to Falador, run east to the park and talk to [[Heskel]] at the tree patch. ([[Ring of Wealth]]'s Falador teleport option takes you there directly). {{Chat option|1Are you a member of the Group of Advanced Gardeners?}}
*Return to the Draynor Village market and talk to Martin. {{Chat option|2Quest.}}}}

===Trouble in Zanaris===
{{Needed|[[dramen staff]] or [[Lunar staff]], and one free inventory space.}}
{{Checklist|
*Travel to [[Zanaris]] (with your [[dramen staff]] or [[Lunar staff]] equipped, enter the small shack south of [[Lumbridge Castle]] in [[Lumbridge Swamp]]). (If you need to collect the [[spade]], enter the shack without the staff equipped first and collect it).
*Run directly south to the throne room and Talk to the Fairy Godfather. {{Chat option|2Where's the Fairy Queen?}}
*Run north of the bank and talk to [[Fairy Nuff]] to get the [[symptoms list]].
*Speak to [[Zandar Horfyre]] on the top floor of the [[Dark Wizards' Tower]] just north of the [[Makeover mage]].}}

===Getting the Magic Secateurs===
{{Needed|[[Fairytale I - Growing Pains#Blessed secateurs|3 assigned items]] (see link), [[secateurs]], [[Ghostspeak amulet]], [[Draynor skull]] (or [[spade]] to dig one)|recommended=[[Salve graveyard teleport]], a filled [[druid pouch]] (so items that may be rotten by ghasts are protected)}}
{{Checklist|
*Speak to [[Malignius Mortifer]], the necromancer north-west of [[Port Sarim]]'s rune shop. {{Chat option|2I need help with fighting a Tanglefoot.}}
*If you do not have [[secateurs]] or a [[spade]], buy them from the farm shop to the north-east.
*If you do not have the [[Draynor skull]], travel to [[Draynor Manor]] and use a [[spade]] on the grave north of the building, but within the fence to receive the [[Draynor skull]].
*Speak to Malignius Mortifer again to receive the list of three items. {{Chat option|2I was asking you about fighting a Tanglefoot...}}
*Collect the [[Fairytale I - Growing Pains#Blessed secateurs|3 randomly-picked items]]. Check the [[quest journal]] to see your list of items to collect.
'''Note:''' Take a filled [[druid pouch]] with you if you have to collect any items that may be rotten by ghasts or they may turn them into [[rotten food]].
*Travel to the [[Nature Grotto]] in [[Mort Myre Swamp]] (use [[Shades of Mort'ton]] minigame teleport, go west, then follow the winding path north over the bridge), equip your Ghostspeak amulet and talk to [[Filliman Tarlock|the Nature Spirit]] inside to receive the [[Magic secateurs]].}}

===Battle the Tanglefoot===
{{Needed|[[dramen staff]], [[magic secateurs]], [[food]], and [[armour]].}}
{{Checklist|
{{Instance}}
*Travel to [[Zanaris]] with your Magic secateurs and prepare for the [[Tanglefoot]] fight.
*Run south of the wheat fields to the Cosmic Altar and squeeze-through the gap in the western wall.
*Equip your Magic secateurs, run to the end of the tunnel and defeat Tanglefoot. (Turn on [[Protect from Melee]] if you have the level for it. You can also lure the Tanglefoot around the mushrooms to the east to be able to [[flinch]] it.)
*Pick up the [[Queen's secateurs]].
*Talk to the [[Fairy Godfather]].}}
'''Congratulations! Quest complete!'''

